Cell[TextData[{
 "for basic information, links and references. Google also notes the \
existence of sites having to do specifically with the application of ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " to problems of this general nature.\n\nHere I will be stumbling along, \
clumsily reinventing the wheel, with a very limited objective.\n\nOne can \
think of a variety of ways to introduce stochastic elements into classical \
(also quantum?) equations of motion. ",
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "I begin with exporation of an idea which is conspicuously ",
 StyleBox["devoid",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " of direct physical motivation, which has only a sentimental circumstance \
to recomment it: it is the idea that I attempted to address in my \
undergraduate thesis."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.531152547833674*^9, 3.5311527366854677`*^9}, {
  3.5311527716144953`*^9, 3.53115286003262*^9}, {3.531152904171369*^9, 
  3.531152978590241*^9}, {3.5311531271021843`*^9, 3.531153194554097*^9}, {
  3.531153230583345*^9, 3.531153240303149*^9}}],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Classical lattice dynamics", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5311532625163393`*^9, 3.531153267594673*^9}}],

Cell["\<\
A particle moves on the phase plane under general control of a Hamiltonian \
H[x, p] not contiuously but in a series of hops (time measured in discrete \
intervals of duration \[Tau]), subject to this constraint: every hop is\
\[LongDash]with equal probability\[LongDash]parallel either to the x-axis or \
the p-axis.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5311537283087387`*^9, 3.531153848941462*^9}, {
  3.531153879617511*^9, 3.531153984457726*^9}}],

